Creating Star Schema Model Data Mart 10

 Below picture tells you about OLTP (Online Transaction Process) and OLAP (Online Analytical Process). We are going to create OLAP Database by implementing Star Schema model.



Before creating Stored Procedure we have to create Data Mart Database in Sql Server Management Studio. Create a Stored Procedure that has different batch of codes they are:

  • Unpivot temptable
  • Single data set temptable
  • Creating 5 Dimension tables using Merge statement applying Slowly Changing Dimension (SCD) type 1 to check new insert or update in Data Mart tables.
  • Creating one Fact table using Merge statement applying Slowly Changing Dimension (SCD) type 1 to check new insert or update in Data Mart tables.

Now download the Stored Procedure file from the attachment and then execute it. This will create 5 Dimensions and 1 Fact table with all the required data. Execute all tables to check all the records. Be patient while executing Stored procedure it will take couple of minutes.

Follow GIF steps, you should successfully create Data Mart:

  • Creating Data Mart Database.
  • Making sure there is no tables.
  • Creating Stored Procedure (execute only the create statement (you will get commands completed successfully) not the sp_executesql usp_LoadEstimateDataDW.
  • Execute Stored Procedure (sp_executesql usp_LoadEstimateDataDW).
  • Querying Fact table to check all the rows got inserted.
